Tammy Petersen, News24KwaZulu-Natal - A motorist was killed on the N2 near Mvoti in Stanger on Friday night when his car collided with a truck, paramedics have confirmed.Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said a team responded to the collision on the highway where they found that the driver of an Uno had been killed in the crash. "The driver of the truck was seriously injured. After medics treated the man at the scene they transported him to a nearby hospital for the care that he required," Botha said in a statement. Authorities were on scene for further investigations. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.